rg und Portugal trieben. Die Studie liefert neue Erkenntnisse zur Geschichte von Migration und interkultureller Begegnung in der frühmodernen Globalisierung.  aWhat impact did the cultural origins and religious backgrounds of the merchants in the early modern period have on their business activities? How did these people manage to integrate themselves into the foreign societies within which they lived and worked? In this book Jorun Poettering examines the circumstances of the merchants who traded between Hamburg and Portugal in the seventeenth century. Her study offers new insights into the history of migration and intercultural encounter as world became more interconnected.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aMerchantszGermanyzHamburgxHistoryy17th century. 0aMerchantszPortugalxHistoryy17th century. 4a17th century. 4aHamburg. 4aMerchants. 4aPortugal. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh  a17th Century.  aHamburg.  aMerchants.  aPortugal.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2019 Part 1z978311076246408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104700170 cprintz978311046993640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047210340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110472103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110472103/original  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK